        public abstract java.lang.String authBaseUrl()
        The base URL for the configured Udini server against which to authenticate. Any trailing slash character must be omitted
        • Bad: https://identity.udini.eu
        • Good: https://identity.udini.eu/
        Defaults to https://identity.udini.eu

        the currently configured value

        • Bad: https://manager.udini.eu
        • Good: https://manager.udini.eu/
        Defaults to https://manager.udini.eu
        Returns:
        the currently configured value

      • backgroundScanningEnabled

        public abstract boolean backgroundScanningEnabled()
        Whether or not scanning should continue in the background. The SDK will detect it when the process moves to the background, it will then check the value returned here in order to determine to continue scanning in the background.

        Defaults to false.
        Returns:
        the currently configured value

      • automaticAccessEnabled

        public abstract boolean automaticAccessEnabled()
        Whether or not the SDK should allow automatic access when the mobile device comes in range of an Udini device configured with an invoke-on-proximity setting.

        When this is true it will allow users to unlock doors and trigger actions by coming in the vicinity of an Udini device, which is particularly convenient for lower-security and frequently accessed gateways.

        Defaults to true.
        Returns:
        the currently configured value

        public abstract long scanReportDelayMillis()
